<TITLE> ASM Ali Kabir made acting establishment secretary </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 13 (bdnews24.com)  ASM Ali Kabir has become acting establishment secretary in a first major civil service decision of the new government The establishment ministry announced the appointmentof Kabir, who had been the chairman of Bangladesh Inland Water Transport Corporation, on Tuesday. A 1979 recruit to Bangladesh Civil Service, Kabir told bdnews24.com he had already assumed the office. The appointment succeeds M Moslehuddin who retired as establishment secretary on Dec. 31, 2008. The past BNP-led government forced him to retire as joint secretary after making him officer on special duty (OSD) for some years. Kabir contested his being sent into forced retirement in the court, which, in turn, ordered his reinstatement. The interim government headed by president Iajuddin Ahmed reinstated him in the job and promoted him from joint secretary to additional secretary
